'''Lamine Yamal Nasraoui Ebana'''{{efn|group=note|{{IPA|es|laˈmiɲ ɟʝaˈmal nasˈraɣwi eˈβana, -ɣwj -|small=no}}; {{IPA|ca|ləˈmin jəˈmal nəzˈrawi əˈβanə|small=no}}.}} (born 13 July 2007) is a Spanish professional [[footballer]] who plays as a [[right winger]] or [[right midfielder]] for {{Spanish football updater|Barcelona}} club [[FC Barcelona|Barcelona]] and the [[Spain national football team|Spain national team]]. Widely regarded as one of the best players in the world, he is known for his flair, chance creation, and long-distance curling goals.<ref name=":4" /><ref name=":8" /><ref name=":10" /><ref name=":11" /><ref>{{cite web |date=6 June 2025 |title=Lamine Yamal's Powerful Response to The Ballon d'Or |url=https://www.beinsports.com/en-us/soccer/uefa-nations-league/articles-video/lamine-yamal-s-powerful-response-to-the-ballon-d-or-2025-06-06 |access-date=6 June 2025 |website=beIN SPORTS}}</ref>

Yamal was a member of the youth academy, [[La Masia]], before breaking into the Barcelona first team squad in the [[2023–24 FC Barcelona season|2023–24]] season. He became the youngest player to be nominated for the [[Ballon d'Or]] (at age 17) and also won the [[Kopa Trophy]] in [[2024 Ballon d'Or|2024]] and [[2025 Ballon d'Or|2025]], presented to the best young player in the world. In the [[2024–25 FC Barcelona season|following season]], he was integral to Barcelona winning a [[domestic treble]] of the La Liga title, the [[Copa del Rey]], and the [[Supercopa de España]]. At 18 years old, Yamal finished as runner-up for the [[2025 Ballon d'Or]].

Yamal has represented Spain internationally at various [[Spain national youth football team|youth levels]], and made his debut for the senior team in 2023, becoming the youngest player to represent and score for the country at age 16. He was selected for [[UEFA Euro 2024]], playing an important role in helping Spain win their fourth title, while also winning the tournament's [[UEFA European Championship awards#Young Player of the Tournament|Young Player Award]]. He holds multiple records in his international career, including the youngest player to appear in a [[List of UEFA European Championship finals|UEFA European Championship final]] (at age 17), the youngest player in a European Championship (at age 16), and the youngest goalscorer in a European Championship (at age 16).<ref>{{Cite web |last=Batlle |first=Nick |date=2026-04-19 |title=Barcelona must do more to maximize the potential of Lamine Yamal |url=https://www.barcablaugranes.com/cant-del-blog-barcelona-opinion/118031/barcelona-must-do-more-to-maximize-the-potential-of-lamine-yamal |access-date=2026-04-19 |website=Barca Blaugranes |language=en-US}}</ref>

==Early life==
Lamine Yamal Nasraoui Ebana was born on 13 July 2007 in [[Esplugues de Llobregat]] in the [[Barcelona metropolitan area]] in [[Catalonia]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Who is Lamine Yamal? Barcelona wonderkid making history in La Liga and for Spain |url=https://www.sportingnews.com/us/soccer/news/lamine-yamal-barcelona-la-liga-spain-records-playing-style/723f032776a836c20966f8ac |website=Sporting News |date=9 July 2024 |access-date=26 July 2024 |archive-date=27 July 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240727031941/https://www.sportingnews.com/us/soccer/news/lamine-yamal-barcelona-la-liga-spain-records-playing-style/723f032776a836c20966f8ac |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name=Corbella>{{Cite web |last=Corbella |first=Enrique|title=Lamine Yamal, el niño de 15 años que ya entrena con el Barcelona: descubre al "mini Messi" de La Masía |url=https://www.marca.com/futbol/barcelona/2022/09/05/6315a6aa268e3ead0d8b4588.html|date=5 September 2022|access-date=6 September 2022|website=[[Marca (newspaper)|Marca]] |language=es |archive-date=6 September 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220906214946/https://www.marca.com/futbol/barcelona/2022/09/05/6315a6aa268e3ead0d8b4588.html }}</ref> He was given a [[compound given name]] to honour two people, named Lamine and Yamal, who helped his family financially shortly before their son was born.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Mumford |first=Robin |date=2024-09-23 |title=The reason why Lamine Yamal wears both names on back of his shirt |url=https://www.givemesport.com/why-lamine-yamal-wears-both-names-on-back-of-his-shirt/ |access-date=2025-03-17 |website=GiveMeSport |language=en}}</ref> Growing up in Mataróin [[Rocafonda]], a neighbourhood described by ''[[El País]]'' as "forgotten, isolated and stigmatized", Yamal started playing football at local club La Torreta in [[Granollers]] at the age of four;<ref name="Herrero">{{cite news |last1=Herrero |first1=Laia Cervelló |title=Lamine Yamal: Barcelona's young prodigy and the proud neighbourhood that shaped him |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/4997511/2023/10/26/barcelona-lamine-yamal-rocafonda-el-clasico/ |website=The New York Times |access-date=10 July 2024 |archive-url=http://web.archive.org/web/20251103002834/https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/4997511/2023/10/26/barcelona-lamine-yamal-rocafonda-el-clasico/ |archive-date= 2025-11-03|date=26 October 2023|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="thetimes">{{cite news |last1=Hawkey |first1=Ian |title=Super-prodigy with 'flashes of Messi': the rise of Spain's Lamine Yamal |url=https://www.thetimes.com/sport/football/article/super-prodigy-with-flashes-of-messi-rise-of-spains-lamine-yamal-rprp5fkfj |website=[[The Times]] |access-date=10 July 2024 |archive-date=25 February 2026 |date=18 June 2024 |archive-url=http://web.archive.org/web/20260225022157/https://www.thetimes.com/sport/football/article/super-prodigy-with-flashes-of-messi-rise-of-spains-lamine-yamal-rprp5fkfj|url-status=live}}</ref> he celebrates goals by making a gesture of the number 304, the last digits of the local postcode 08304. Following his success, his popularisation of the number has been credited with bringing pride and recognition to the working class community of Rocafonda.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Guevara |first1=Irene |title=Rocafonda, the neighborhood that regained its pride thanks to soccer sensation Lamine Yamal |url=https://english.elpais.com/sports/2024-07-11/rocafonda-the-neighborhood-that-regained-its-pride-thanks-to-soccer-sensation-lamine-yamal.html |access-date=13 July 2024 |work=El País |date=11 July 2024 |archive-date=17 July 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240717135436/https://english.elpais.com/sports/2024-07-11/rocafonda-the-neighborhood-that-regained-its-pride-thanks-to-soccer-sensation-lamine-yamal.html |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Lamine Yamal: Barcelona football star inspires youth in hometown Rocafonda |url=https://www.aljazeera.com/sports/2025/5/25/lamine-yamal-barcelona-football-star-inspires-youth-in-hometown-rocafonda |date=25 May 2025 |archive-url=http://web.archive.org/web/20260210101002/https://www.aljazeera.com/sports/2025/5/25/lamine-yamal-barcelona-football-star-inspires-youth-in-hometown-rocafonda |archive-date= 2026-02-10|work=Al Jazeera |last=Keeley |first=Graham }}</ref>

At six years old, Yamal was scouted by [[FC Barcelona|Barcelona]] and was invited to training sessions at [[La Masia]], signing for the club in 2014 moving to Barcelona to live and train at the academy.<ref name="espn" /><ref name=":1">{{Cite web|last1=Picó|first1=Diego|last2=Gillingham|first2=Geoff|title=Lamine Yamal shows shades of Messi|url=https://www.marca.com/en/football/barcelona/2019/12/28/5e072c5722601dbe358b45a6.html |url-status=live|date=28 December 2019|access-date=6 September 2022|website=Marca|archive-date=9 September 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220909141431/https://www.marca.com/en/football/barcelona/2019/12/28/5e072c5722601dbe358b45a6.html }}</ref> Growing up, Yamal's footballing idols were [[Ronaldinho]], [[Lionel Messi]], and [[Neymar]].<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.90min.com/lamine-yamal-names-three-barcelona-legends-footballing-idols | title=Lamine Yamal names three Barcelona legends as his footballing idols | date=17 December 2024 }}</ref> Yamal met Messi as a six-month old baby in a photoshoot.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Riddell |first=Ben Morse, Don |date=2024-07-14 |title=‘One in a billion’: Photographer who captured Lionel Messi with a baby Lamine Yamal details rare shoot after photos resurface |url=https://www.cnn.com/2024/07/14/sport/lamine-yamal-lionel-messi-photoshoot-2007-spt-intl |access-date=2026-04-26 |website=CNN |language=en}}</ref>

== Club career ==

=== Youth career ===
Growing up through the youth ranks of [[La Masia]], Yamal was soon viewed as one of the academy's best prospects.<ref name=":1" /> Initially added to the [[FC Barcelona (youth)|Juvenil A]] team – already above his age grade – for the [[2022–23 FC Barcelona season|2022–23 season]],<ref>{{Cite web|first=Ferran|last=Martínez|title=Julián Araujo, un 'tapado' para el lateral derecho |url=https://www.mundodeportivo.com/futbol/fc-barcelona/20220831/1001859973/julian-araujo-tapado-lateral-derecho.html|date=31 August 2022|access-date=6 September 2022|website=[[Mundo Deportivo]]|language=es |archive-date=9 September 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220909141437/https://www.mundodeportivo.com/futbol/fc-barcelona/20220831/1001859973/julian-araujo-tapado-lateral-derecho.html |url-status=live }}</ref> Yamal was selected by [[Xavi (footballer, born 1980)|Xavi]] to train with the first team along with other youngsters in early September 2022.<ref name=Corbella /><ref name=":2">{{Cite web|title=FC Barcelona: Wird Lamine Yamal (15) der nächste Lionel Messi? |url=https://sportbild.bild.de/fussball/la-liga/primera-division/fc-barcelona-wird-lamine-yamal-15-der-naechste-lionel-messi-81228506.sport.html |url-status=live |website=[[Sport Bild]]|date=5 September 2022|access-date=6 September 2022|language=de|archive-date=9 September 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220909141433/https://sportbild.bild.de/fussball/la-liga/primera-division/fc-barcelona-wird-lamine-yamal-15-der-naechste-lionel-messi-81228506.sport.html }}</ref> While still yet to sign his first professional contract with the club, he appeared to be one of the academy members to most impress the coach.<ref name=":3">{{Cite web|first=Jonathan|last=Fernández|title=La Masía alumbra a su 'nuevo Ansu' |url=https://as.com/futbol/primera/la-masia-alumbra-a-su-nuevo-ansu-n/|website=[[Diario AS]]|date=4 September 2022|access-date=6 September 2022|language=es|archive-date=5 September 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220905220002/https://as.com/futbol/primera/la-masia-alumbra-a-su-nuevo-ansu-n/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=5 September 2022 |title=Promessa de 15 anos encanta Xavi e treina com elenco do Barcelona |url=https://ge.globo.com/futebol/futebol-internacional/noticia/2022/09/05/promessa-de-15-anos-encanta-xavi-e-treina-com-elenco-do-barcelona.ghtml|website=[[TV Globo|Globo Esporte]]|access-date=6 September 2022 |language=pt|archive-date=5 September 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220905140033/https://ge.globo.com/futebol/futebol-internacional/noticia/2022/09/05/promessa-de-15-anos-encanta-xavi-e-treina-com-elenco-do-barcelona.ghtml |url-status=live }}</ref>

Yamal made his first-team debut on 29 April 2023, replacing [[Gavi (footballer)|Gavi]] in the 83rd minute of a 4–0 victory against [[Real Betis]] in [[La Liga]], in which he registered a shot on target and became the fifth youngest player in La Liga's history at 15 years, 9 months, and 16 days old,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.90min.com/posts/youngest-players-in-history-la-liga |title=Youngest players in the history of La Liga |website=www.90min.com |date=2 May 2023 |access-date=15 February 2024 |archive-date=15 February 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240215235918/https://www.90min.com/posts/youngest-players-in-history-la-liga |url-status=live }}</ref> and the youngest to appear for Barcelona's first team since the 15-year-old [[Armando Sagi]] in 1922, over a century before.<ref>{{cite web|first=Tom|last=Sanderson|title=15-Year-Old FC Barcelona Prodigy Lamine Yamal Smashes Youngest Appearance Maker Record|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/tomsanderson/2023/04/29/15-year-old-prodigy-lamine-yamal-smashes-fc-barcelona-youngest-appearance-maker-record/|work=[[Forbes]]|access-date=29 April 2023|archive-date=10 May 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230510022802/https://www.forbes.com/sites/tomsanderson/2023/04/29/15-year-old-prodigy-lamine-yamal-smashes-fc-barcelona-youngest-appearance-maker-record/|url-status=live}}</ref> He won his first title with Barça on 14 May 2023, having been part of the squad that won the [[2022–23 La Liga]],<ref>{{cite web|first=Carlos|last=Montenegro|title=Lamine Yamal enters the history of LaLiga after the Barça title |url=https://www.fcbarcelonanoticias.com/en/players/lamine-yamal-enters-the-history-of-laliga-after-the-barca-title_292382_102.html|website=FC Barcelona Noticias|date=15 May 2023 |access-date=22 August 2023 |archive-date=22 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230822070119/https://www.fcbarcelonanoticias.com/en/players/lamine-yamal-enters-the-history-of-laliga-after-the-barca-title_292382_102.html |url-status=live }}</ref> but missed the title celebration the following week due to international duty with Spain.<ref>{{cite web |title=The players who helped Barcelona win LaLiga: Lamine Yamal not included|url=https://en.as.com/soccer/the-players-who-helped-barcelona-win-laliga-lamine-yamal-not-included-n/|website=Diario AS|date=15 May 2023 |access-date=22 August 2023 |archive-date=22 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230822070117/https://en.as.com/soccer/the-players-who-helped-barcelona-win-laliga-lamine-yamal-not-included-n/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

=== 2023–24: First team breakthrough ===
Although Yamal remained on the [[FC Barcelona Atlètic|Barcelona Atlètic]] squad throughout the season,<ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-02-25 |title=Barça Atlètic Squad - FC Barcelona Official Channel |url=https://www.fcbarcelona.com/en/football/barca-b/players |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240225194746/https://www.fcbarcelona.com/en/football/barca-b/players |url-status=dead |archive-date=2024-02-25 |access-date=2024-07-15 }}</ref> he earned his first start for the club on 20 August 2023 in a 2–0 victory over [[Cádiz CF|Cádiz]] at the [[Estadi Olímpic Lluís Companys]].<ref name="youngstart">{{Cite web|title=Lamine Yamal, youngest FC Barcelona starter ever|url=https://www.fcbarcelona.com/en/football/first-team/news/3644506/lamine-yamal-youngest-fc-barcelona-starter-ever|website=[[FC Barcelona]]|date=21 August 2023 |access-date=22 August 2023 |archive-date=22 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230822070123/https://www.fcbarcelona.com/en/football/first-team/news/3644506/lamine-yamal-youngest-fc-barcelona-starter-ever |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|first=Thomas|last=Schlachter|title=Lamine Yamal becomes youngest La Liga starter in 21st century in Barcelona's 2-0 win against Cádiz|url=https://edition.cnn.com/2023/08/21/sport/lamine-yamal-youngest-starter-barcelona-spt-intl/index.html|website=[[CNN]]|date=21 August 2023|access-date=22 August 2023|archive-date=10 October 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231010190438/https://edition.cnn.com/2023/08/21/sport/lamine-yamal-youngest-starter-barcelona-spt-intl/index.html |url-status=live }}</ref> His first start was met with a standing ovation as he was subbed off with five minutes left in the game.<ref>{{cite web|first=Pol|last=Ballús|title=Yamal shines again for Barcelona as Xavi turns to 'fearless' 16-year-old in attack |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/4792442/2023/08/21/barcelona-lamine-yamal-ansu-fati-xavi-cadiz/|website=[[The Athletic]]|date=22 August 2023|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240618224610/https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/4792442/2023/08/21/barcelona-lamine-yamal-ansu-fati-xavi-cadiz/ |archive-date=18 June 2024}}</ref> In his next starting appearance, Yamal was named [[Player of the match|man of the match]] after contributing towards two goals scored by [[Gavi (footballer)|Gavi]] and [[Robert Lewandowski]] in a 4–3 victory over [[Villarreal CF|Villarreal]] on 28 August.<ref>{{cite web|title=Villarreal 3–4 FC Barcelona: Rollercoaster ride to victory |url=https://www.fcbarcelona.com/en/football/first-team/news/3655925/villarreal-3-4-fc-barcelona-rollercoaster-ride-to-victory |website=FC Barcelona|date=28 August 2023 |access-date=27 August 2023 |archive-date=2 September 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230902073111/https://www.fcbarcelona.com/en/football/first-team/news/3655925/villarreal-3-4-fc-barcelona-rollercoaster-ride-to-victory |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Watch: 16-year-old Lamine Yamal's highlights after incredible Barcelona performance |url=https://www.football-espana.net/2023/08/27/watch-16-year-old-lamine-yamals-highlights-after-incredible-barcelona-performance |website=Football España|date=27 August 2023 |access-date=27 August 2023 |archive-date=31 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230831184215/https://www.football-espana.net/2023/08/27/watch-16-year-old-lamine-yamals-highlights-after-incredible-barcelona-performance |url-status=live }}</ref> He was named the inaugural [[La Liga Player of the Month#La Liga U23 Player of the Month|U23 Player of the Month]] for August as a result of his performances.<ref name=":7">{{cite news |date=8 September 2023 |title=Lamine Yamal, Best LaLiga EA Sports U23 Player in August |url=https://www.laliga.com/en-US/news/lamine-yamal-best-laliga-ea-sports-u23-player-in-august |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230908193726/https://www.laliga.com/en-US/news/lamine-yamal-best-laliga-ea-sports-u23-player-in-august |archive-date=8 September 2023 |access-date=8 September 2023 |publisher=La Liga}}</ref> On 19 September, Yamal made his [[2023–24 UEFA Champions League|Champions League]] debut in a 5–0 victory over [[Royal Antwerp F.C.|Royal Antwerp]].<ref name="youngcl">{{cite web |date=19 September 2023 |title=Youngest Champions League players: Moukoko, Yamal, Babayaro, Cherki, Halilović, Tielemans |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/news/0253-0d042a009474-d3a14de143a9-1000--youngest-champions-league-players-moukoko-yamal-babayaro-che/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230928115651/https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/news/0253-0d042a009474-d3a14de143a9-1000--youngest-champions-league-players-moukoko-yamal-babayaro-che/ |archive-date=28 September 2023 |access-date=19 September 2023 |publisher=[[UEFA]]}}</ref> 

On 2 October 2023, Yamal extended his contract with Barcelona until 2026, with a buyout clause of €1 billion.<ref>{{cite web |date=2 October 2023 |title=Lamine Yamal extends contract to 2026 |url=https://www.fcbarcelona.com/en/football/barca-b/news/3714997/lamine-yamal-extends-contract-to-2026 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231004153504/https://www.fcbarcelona.com/en/football/barca-b/news/3714997/lamine-yamal-extends-contract-to-2026 |archive-date=4 October 2023 |access-date=2 October 2023 |publisher=FC Barcelona}}</ref> Two days later, he started in his first match of the Champions League against [[FC Porto|Porto]].<ref name=":6" /> On 8 October, he scored his first goal for the first team in a 2–2 away draw to [[Granada CF|Granada]] and made his first [[El Clásico]] appearance as a substitute in a 2–1 loss at home on 28 October.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Lamine Yamal |url=https://www.fcbarcelona.com/en/football/barca-b/players/3673478/ |access-date=28 March 2024 |publisher=FC Barcelona Atlètic |archive-date=17 March 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240317125534/https://www.fcbarcelona.com/en/football/barca-b/players/3673478/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name=":9" /> On 4 December, Yamal was given the inaugural Golden Boy The Youngest trophy, which is awarded to the youngest player nominated for the [[Golden Boy (award)|Golden Boy award]].<ref>{{cite web |date=4 December 2023 |title=Lamine Yamal and Aitana Bonmatí receive Golden Boy 2023 awards |url=https://www.fcbarcelona.com/en/news/3808039/lamine-yamal-and-aitana-bonmati-receive-golden-boy-2023-awards |access-date=8 December 2023 |publisher=FC Barcelona |archive-date=25 July 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240725002151/https://www.fcbarcelona.com/en/news/3808039/lamine-yamal-and-aitana-bonmati-receive-golden-boy-2023-awards |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |date=5 September 2023 |title='I will like to win it': Yamal makes promise after receiving prestigious award |url=https://tribuna.com/en/news/fcbarcelona-2023-12-05-i-will-like-to-win-it-yamal-makes-promise-after-receiving-prestigious-award/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231208154209/https://tribuna.com/en/news/fcbarcelona-2023-12-05-i-will-like-to-win-it-yamal-makes-promise-after-receiving-prestigious-award/ |archive-date=8 December 2023 |access-date=8 December 2023 |website=Tribuna}}</ref> Subsequently, on the ceremony day, Yamal was not present due to school.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Tournoux |first1=Manu |date=5 December 2023 |title=Lamine Yamal didn't go to Golden Boy because he had school! |url=https://frenchfootballweekly.com/2023/12/05/lamine-yamal-didnt-go-to-golden-boy-because-he-had-school/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231208134513/https://frenchfootballweekly.com/2023/12/05/lamine-yamal-didnt-go-to-golden-boy-because-he-had-school/ |archive-date=8 December 2023 |access-date=8 December 2023 |website=French Football Weekly}}</ref>

On 11 January 2024, Yamal scored in a 2–0 win over [[CA Osasuna|Osasuna]] in the [[2024 Supercopa de España|semi-final]] of the [[Supercopa de España]], becoming the youngest player to score in the Supercopa, at 16 years and 182 days.<ref name="goalsensation">{{Cite web |date=11 January 2024 |title=Watch: Lamine Yamal making more history! 16-year-old Barcelona sensation breaks Supercopa goalscoring record after late strike against Osasuna |url=https://www.goal.com/en/lists/watch-lamine-yamal-history-16-year-old-barcelona-sensation-supercopa-goalscoring-record-osasuna/bltd41eed3f97af8ab6 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240111223729/https://www.goal.com/en/lists/watch-lamine-yamal-history-16-year-old-barcelona-sensation-supercopa-goalscoring-record-osasuna/bltd41eed3f97af8ab6 |archive-date=11 January 2024 |access-date=10 February 2024 |website=[[Goal (website)|Goal]]}}</ref> Yamal then played the last 29 minutes of the [[2024 Supercopa de España final|final]] against [[Real Madrid CF|Real Madrid]] on 14 January.<ref>{{Cite web |date=15 January 2024 |title=Real Madrid 4–1 FC Barcelona: Super Cup defeat |url=https://www.fcbarcelona.com/en/football/first-team/news/3857625/real-madrid-4-1-fc-barcelona-super-cup-defeat |access-date=10 July 2024 |website= |publisher=FC Barcelona |archive-date=27 January 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240127053209/https://www.fcbarcelona.com/en/football/first-team/news/3857625/real-madrid-4-1-fc-barcelona-super-cup-defeat |url-status=live }}</ref> Two weeks later, on 25 January, he scored in the [[Copa del Rey]] quarter-finals against [[Athletic Bilbao]] in an eventual 4–2 loss after extra time, becoming the youngest goalscorer in the competition's history.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Clark |first=Gill |date=25 January 2024 |title=Lamine Yamal apologises to Barcelona fans after Copa del Rey defeat to Athletic |url=https://www.barcablaugranes.com/2024/1/25/24050130/lamine-yamal-apologises-to-barcelona-fans-after-copa-del-rey-defeat-to-athletic |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240125120608/https://www.barcablaugranes.com/2024/1/25/24050130/lamine-yamal-apologises-to-barcelona-fans-after-copa-del-rey-defeat-to-athletic |archive-date=25 January 2024 |access-date=10 February 2024 |website=Barca Blaugranes}}</ref> On 11 February, Yamal scored his first brace in a 3–3 draw against [[Granada CF|Granada]], earning the man of the match.<ref>{{Cite web |date=11 February 2024 |title=FC Barcelona 3-3 Granada: Held at home in six-goal thriller |url=https://www.fcbarcelona.com/en/football/first-team/news/3892232/fc-barcelona-3-3-granada-held-at-home-in-six-goal-thriller |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240229055747/https://www.fcbarcelona.com/en/football/first-team/news/3892232/fc-barcelona-3-3-granada-held-at-home-in-six-goal-thriller |archive-date=29 February 2024 |access-date=12 February 2024 |website=FC Barcelona}}</ref> In the [[2023–24 FC Barcelona season|2023–24 season]], Barcelona finished second in La Liga and ended their Champions League run at the quarter-finals after being knocked out by [[Paris Saint-Germain FC|Paris Saint-Germain]], against whom Yamal registered an assist in the second leg, which they lost 4–1.<ref>{{cite web |title=Sevilla 1-2 FC Barcelona: Winning end to the season |url=https://www.fcbarcelona.com/en/news/4028501/sevilla-1-2-fc-barcelona-winning-end-to-the-season |publisher=FC Barcelona |access-date=10 July 2024|date=27 May 2024}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Barcelona 1-4 Paris St-Germain (Agg: 4-6): Kylian Mbappe scores twice as PSG reach last four |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/68819301 |website=BBC Sport |access-date=10 July 2024 |date=15 April 2024 |archive-date=1 June 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240601224314/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/68819301 |url-status=live }}</ref>

At 16 years of age, Yamal broke several records for Barcelona during the season, making 50 appearances in all competitions.<ref>{{cite web |title=All Lamine Yamal's records |url=https://www.fcbarcelona.com/en/football/first-team/news/4032517/all-lamine-yamals-records |publisher=FC Barcelona |access-date=10 July 2024 |date=10 July 2024 |archive-date=25 July 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240725002117/https://www.fcbarcelona.com/en/football/first-team/news/4032517/all-lamine-yamals-records |url-status=live }}</ref> In La Liga, Yamal became the youngest starter for Barcelona,<ref name="youngstart"/> the youngest player to record an assist,<ref>{{cite web |date=28 August 2023 |title=Lamine Yamal, a diamond in the making |url=https://www.fcbarcelona.com/en/news/3655761/lamine-yamal-a-diamond-in-the-making |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230827211329/https://www.fcbarcelona.com/en/news/3655761/lamine-yamal-a-diamond-in-the-making |archive-date=27 August 2023 |access-date=27 August 2023 |website=FC Barcelona}}</ref> the youngest to score for Barcelona and in La Liga,<ref name="FCByoung">{{Cite web |date=8 October 2023 |title=Lamine Yamal, youngest Liga goalscorer of all time |url=https://www.fcbarcelona.com/en/football/first-team/news/3731136/lamine-yamal-youngest-liga-goalscorer-of-all-time/featured |access-date=8 October 2023 |publisher=FC Barcelona|archive-date=10 October 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231010214502/https://www.fcbarcelona.com/en/football/first-team/news/3731136/lamine-yamal-youngest-liga-goalscorer-of-all-time/featured |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Ballús |first=Pol |date=8 October 2023 |title=Yamal becomes youngest scorer in La Liga history |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/4942408/2023/10/08/lamine-yamal-barcelona-la-liga-scorer/ |access-date=8 October 2023 |publisher=The Athletic|archive-date=10 October 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231010214503/https://theathletic.com/4942408/2023/10/08/lamine-yamal-barcelona-la-liga-scorer/ |url-status=live }}</ref> the youngest player to feature for Barcelona in El Clásico,<ref name=":9">{{cite web |url=https://www.fcbarcelona.com/en/football/first-team/news/3754181/lamine-yamal-youngest-player-to-feature-in-a-clasico/featured |title=Lamine Yamal, youngest player to feature in a Clásico |website=FC Barcelona |date=28 October 2023 |access-date=28 October 2023 |archive-date=29 October 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231029182445/https://www.fcbarcelona.com/en/football/first-team/news/3754181/lamine-yamal-youngest-player-to-feature-in-a-clasico/featured |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name="preco">{{cite web |url=https://www.sport.es/es/noticias/barca/albeniz-precocidad-clasico-12348620 |title=Albéniz, la precocidad y el clásico |trans-title=Albéniz, precocity and the classic|website=Sport.es|date=23 October 2021 |access-date=15 February 2024|language=es|archive-date=22 April 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220422141754/https://www.sport.es/es/noticias/barca/albeniz-precocidad-clasico-12348620 |url-status=live }}</ref> and the youngest player to score a brace in La Liga and first player ever to achieve this record under the age of 17.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.fcbarcelona.com/en/football/first-team/news/3892874/lamine-yamal-youngest-player-to-score-twice-in-a-la-liga-match |title=Lamine Yamal youngest player to score twice in a LaLiga match |publisher=FC Barcelona |date=12 February 2024 |access-date=13 February 2024 |archive-date=13 February 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240213010926/https://www.fcbarcelona.com/en/football/first-team/news/3892874/lamine-yamal-youngest-player-to-score-twice-in-a-la-liga-match |url-status=live }}</ref> He also became the youngest player to register more than ten goal contributions in La Liga at 16 years and 213 days.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Lamine Yamal Becomes Youngest Player Ever To Register 10+ Goals And Assists In One Season|url=https://news.abplive.com/sports/football/lamine-yamal-becomes-youngest-player-ever-to-register-10-goals-and-assists-in-one-season-1664009|website=ABP Live|date=12 February 2024|access-date=13 February 2024|archive-date=24 July 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240724230739/https://news.abplive.com/sports/football/lamine-yamal-becomes-youngest-player-ever-to-register-10-goals-and-assists-in-one-season-1664009|url-status=live}}</ref> In the Champions League, Yamal became the second youngest player to feature in the cup (behind [[Youssoufa Moukoko]]),<ref name="youngcl"/> the youngest player named in a starting line-up,<ref name=":6">{{cite web |url=https://www.fcbarcelona.com/en/football/first-team/news/3721123/lamine-yamal-youngest-starter-ever-in-the-champions-league |title=Lamine Yamal, youngest starter ever in the Champions League |publisher=FC Barcelona |date=4 October 2023 |access-date=4 October 2023 |archive-date=5 October 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231005015703/https://www.fcbarcelona.com/en/football/first-team/news/3721123/lamine-yamal-youngest-starter-ever-in-the-champions-league |url-status=live }}</ref> and the youngest player to play in the knockout phase.<ref>{{cite web |date=21 February 2024 |title=Barcelona's Lamine Yamal makes Champions League history vs Napoli |url=https://onefootball.com/en/news/barcelonas-lamine-yamal-makes-champions-league-history-vs-napoli-39086192 |publisher=[[OneFootball]] |access-date=21 February 2024 |archive-date=25 July 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240725002155/https://onefootball.com/en/news/barcelonas-lamine-yamal-makes-champions-league-history-vs-napoli-39086192 |url-status=live }}</ref>

=== 2024–25: Domestic treble ===
In the first match of the [[2024–25 La Liga|2024–25 La Liga season]] on 18 August, Yamal assisted Lewandowski to help Barcelona equalize against [[Valencia CF|Valencia]] in a 2–1 win.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Valencia vs Barcelona |url=https://www.sofascore.com/football/match/valencia-barcelona/rgbsDgb |access-date=September 17, 2024 |website=[[Sofascore]] |archive-date=17 September 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240917183032/https://www.sofascore.com/football/match/valencia-barcelona/rgbsDgb |url-status=live }}</ref> In the following match against [[Athletic Bilbao]] on 24 August, Yamal scored his first goal of the season in another 2–1 victory.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Barcelona vs Athletic Club |url=https://www.sofascore.com/football/match/athletic-club-barcelona/rgbsAgb#id:12437652 |access-date=September 17, 2024 |website=[[Sofascore]] |archive-date=17 September 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240917183032/https://www.sofascore.com/football/match/athletic-club-barcelona/rgbsAgb#id:12437652 |url-status=live }}</ref> On 19 September, Yamal scored his first Champions League goal, scoring an equalizer in a 2–1 loss to [[AS Monaco|Monaco]] in the [[2024–25 UEFA Champions League league phase|Champions League league phase]], becoming the second youngest scorer in Champions League history at 17 years and 68 days, behind teammate [[Ansu Fati]], who scored at 17 years and 40 days in October 2020.<ref>{{cite web |date=19 September 2024 |title=Lamine Yamal makes history again |url=https://www.fcbarcelona.com/en/football/first-team/news/4122787/lamine-yamal-makes-history-again |access-date=27 September 2024 |website=[[FC Barcelona]] |language=en |archive-date=21 September 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240921025836/https://www.fcbarcelona.com/en/football/first-team/news/4122787/lamine-yamal-makes-history-again |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/c04ppddv50et |title=Monaco 2-1 Barcelona: George Ilenikhena scores as 10-man Barca beaten in Champions League |publisher=[[BBC Sport]] |date=19 September 2024 |access-date=20 September 2024 |first=Marissa |last=Thomas |archive-date=20 September 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240920004524/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/c04ppddv50et |url-status=live }}</ref> On 26 October, at the age of 17 years and 105 days, Yamal became the youngest goalscorer in El Clásico history when he scored the third goal in a 4-0 victory against Real Madrid, surpassing the record of Fati who did so at the age of 17 years and 359 days in October 2020. During the match at the [[Santiago Bernabeu Stadium|Santiago Bernabeu]], Yamal and his teammates Fati and [[Raphinha]] were targeted with racial abuse by a group of home supporters.<ref>{{cite web |date= 26 October 2024 |title=Lamine Yamal youngest Clásico goalscorer|url=https://www.fcbarcelona.com/en/news/4156854/lamine-yamal-youngest-clasico-goalscorer |access-date=28 October 2024 |website=[[FC Barcelona]]|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|date=26 October 2024|title='No place for these criminals in our society!' - Vinicius Junior sends support to Lamine Yamal, Raphinha & Ansu Fati after seeing Barcelona trio targeted with racist insults in El Clasico win at Real Madrid|url=https://www.goal.com/en/lists/no-place-criminals-society-vinicius-junior-sends-support-lamine-yamal-raphinha-ansu-fati-barcelona-trio-targeted-racist-insults-el-clasico-real-madrid/blt051e17049c4c2523#cs5523e9e83afd302b|access-date=28 October 2024|website=[[goal.com]]|language=en|archive-date=3 November 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241103203326/https://www.goal.com/en/lists/no-place-criminals-society-vinicius-junior-sends-support-lamine-yamal-raphinha-ansu-fati-barcelona-trio-targeted-racist-insults-el-clasico-real-madrid/blt051e17049c4c2523#cs5523e9e83afd302b|url-status=live}}</ref> After scoring in a 5-0 victory against [[Valencia CF|Valencia]] in the [[2024–25 Copa del Rey#Quarter-finals|Copa del Rey quarterfinals]] on 6 February 2025, Yamal then underwent a period of poor form, failing to score at all for the next month and five days.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Lamine Yamal Silences Critics with Stunning Goal After Month-Long Drought |url=https://www.beinsports.com/en-us/soccer/uefa-champions-league/articles-video/lamine-yamal-silences-critics-with-stunning-goal-after-month-long-drought-2025-03-12|access-date=2026-03-08 |website=BeIn Sports}}</ref> His goalscoring drought in La Liga, beginning after 26 October 2024, extended to 18 March 2025,<ref>{{Cite web |title=Lamine Yamal sends message to critics after ending La Liga Goal Drought|url=https://www.thesportsfire.com/lamine-yamal-sends-message-to-critics-after-ending-la-liga-goal-drought/|access-date=2026-03-08 |website=The Sports Fire}}</ref> prompting [[Francesco Totti]] to label him a player who scores "few goals".<ref>{{Cite web |title='He still scores few goals' - Barcelona wonderkid Lamine Yamal accused of 'dropping a bit' after goal drought as Italy legend Francesco Totti has his say on teenager's big problem|url=https://www.goal.com/en-gb/lists/barcelona-wonderkid-lamine-yamal-accused-la-liga-francesco-totti-teenager-form/blt6b745bc78ac6d499|access-date=2026-03-08 |website=Goal}}</ref> During this period, manager [[Hansi Flick]] defended him, stating: "Everyone wants to score, but he creates a lot of chances. The important thing is that the team scores, not who scores."<ref>{{Cite web |title=Why Lamine Yamal’s La Liga goal drought does not concern Barcelona – with teenage wonderkid still contributing significantly to bids for three more trophies|url=https://www.goal.com/en-gb/lists/lamine-yamal-la-liga-goal-drought-concern-barcelona-teenage-wonderkid-bids-three-trophies/blt5f60b5ea7c64f9ac|access-date=2026-03-08 |website=Goal}}</ref> On 30 April, Yamal made his 100th appearance for the club in the Champions League semi-final first-leg against [[Inter Milan]]. He scored the first goal in a [[2024–25 UEFA Champions League#Semi-finals|3–3]] draw and was praised by Inter manager [[Simone Inzaghi]], who called Yamal "a phenomenon born every 50 years".<ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-04-30 |title=Inzaghi: Phenoms like Yamal 'born every 50 years' |url=https://africa.espn.com/football/story/_/id/44939974/inter-inzaghi-barcelona-yamal-born-every-50-years |access-date=2025-05-01 |website=ESPN.com |language=en |archive-date=1 May 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250501000322/https://africa.espn.com/football/story/_/id/44939974/inter-inzaghi-barcelona-yamal-born-every-50-years |url-status=live }}</ref>

On 11 May 2025, Yamal played a pivotal role in Barcelona's 4–3 comeback victory over Real Madrid at the Estadi Olímpic Lluís Companys. After trailing 0–2, due to an early brace from [[Kylian Mbappé]], Barcelona responded with goals from [[Eric García (footballer, born 2001)|Eric García]], Yamal, and a brace by Raphinha. Yamal's goal, a curling shot into the bottom corner, levelled the score at 2–2 and was instrumental in shifting the momentum of the match.<ref>{{cite web |title=Barcelona edge closer to title with thrilling 4-3 win over Real Madrid |url=https://www.reuters.com/sports/soccer/barcelona-edge-closer-title-with-thrilling-4-3-win-over-real-madrid-2025-05-11/ |website=Reuters |date=11 May 2025 |access-date=12 May 2025 |archive-date=12 May 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250512084442/https://www.reuters.com/sports/soccer/barcelona-edge-closer-title-with-thrilling-4-3-win-over-real-madrid-2025-05-11/ |url-status=live}}</ref> The victory marked Barcelona's fourth consecutive Clásico win of the season and brought them within one win of clinching the La Liga title.<ref>{{cite web |title=Barcelona 4-3 Real Madrid: Hosts win thriller despite Kylian Mbappe hat-trick |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/c62x2g9d9dgt |website=BBC Sport |date=11 May 2025 |access-date=12 May 2025}}</ref> Yamal's performances during the season provoked some claims by pundits and players that he was the best player in the world.<ref name=":4">{{Cite news |last1=Kay |first1=Oliver |last2=James |first2=Stuart |last3=more |date=2025-05-02 |title=Is Lamine Yamal already the best footballer in Europe? And if not, who is? |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/6326382/2025/05/02/lamine-yamal-best-footballer-who-is/ |access-date=2025-05-17 |work=The New York Times |language=en-US |issn=0362-4331}}</ref><ref name=":8">{{Cite web |date=2025-05-15 |title=Palmer: Yamal is world's best, I love watching him |url=https://www.espn.co.uk/football/story/_/id/45165709/cole-palmer-lamine-yamal-world-best-love-watching-him |access-date=2025-05-17 |website=ESPN.com |language=en}}</ref><ref name=":10">{{Cite web |last=Ukpai |first=Kingsley |date=2025-05-15 |title=Pedri, Raphinha and Flick crown Lamine Yamal best player in the world |url=https://tribuna.com/en/news/2025-05-15-pedri-raphinha-and-flick-crown-lamine-yamal-best-player-in-the-world/ |access-date=2025-05-17 |website=Tribuna.com}}</ref><ref name=":11">{{Cite web |last=Flynn |first=Henry |title=Lamine Yamal Might Be The World's Best—Good Job He's Not Too Fussed |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/henryflynn/2025/05/16/lamine-yamal-might-be-the-worlds-best-good-job-hes-not-too-bothered/ |access-date=2025-05-18 |website=Forbes |language=en}}</ref> He won the 2025 [[Kopa Trophy]], becoming the first footballer to claim it twice, and ranked 2nd in the 2025 [[Ballon d'Or|Ballon d’Or]].<ref>https://www.marca.com/en/football/2025/09/22/68d167ff7aeb1c2f75b9e9e8-live.html</ref>

=== 2025–26: Inheriting number 10 ===
On 27 May 2025, Yamal agreed to his first long-term contract with Barcelona, tying him to the club until 30 June 2031 and to be signed upon his eighteenth birthday.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-05-27 |title=Lamine Yamal extends contract with FC Barcelona to 2031 |url=https://www.fcbarcelona.com/en/football/first-team/news/4274403/lamine-yamal-extends-contract-with-fc-barcelona-to-2031 |access-date=2025-05-28 |website= |publisher=FC Barcelona |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Sung |first=Patrick |date=2025-05-28 |title=17-year-old superstar Lamine Yamal signs contract extension with Barcelona until 2031 |url=https://www.cnn.com/2025/05/28/sport/lamine-yamal-contract-extension-barcelona-2031-spt |access-date=2025-05-28 |website= |publisher=[[CNN]] |language=en-US}}</ref> ''[[The Athletic]]'' reported that Yamal's contract could potentially reach a value of $45.3m per year gross, including wages, bonuses and contract fees, making him one of Barcelona's top-paid players.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Ballús |first=Pol |date=2025-05-28 |title=Lamine Yamal's new Barcelona contract: Inside the deal that could be worth nearly €40m a year |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/6384986/2025/05/28/lamine-yamal-new-barcelona-contract-40m/ |access-date=2025-06-06 |work=The New York Times |language=en-US |issn=0362-4331}}</ref> On 16 July, at the contract signature event, Yamal was presented with Barcelona's [[Squad number (association football)|number 10]] shirt, which had been vacated upon [[Ansu Fati]]'s loan to [[AS Monaco FC|Monaco]].<ref>{{Cite news |date=2025-07-16 |title=Lamine Yamal is the FC Barcelona No.10 |url=https://www.fcbarcelona.com/en/football/first-team/news/4314453/lamine-yamal-is-the-fc-barcelona-no10 |access-date=2025-07-16 |work=FC Barcelona |language=en-US}}</ref>
On 16 August, in the first match of the La Liga season against [[RCD Mallorca|Mallorca]], he scored his first goal for Barcelona while wearing the number 10 shirt.<ref>https://www.goal.com/en-qa/lists/barcelona-player-ratings-vs-mallorca-raphinha-ferran-torres-lamine-yamal-marcus-rashford-la-liga-debut/blt0c3584db573f5335</ref> On 28 February 2026, Yamal scored his first career hat-trick in a 4–1 home win over [[Villarreal CF|Villarreal]].<ref>https://en.as.com/soccer/barcelona-vs-villarreal-live-online-score-stats-goals-updates-laliga-202526-f202602-n/</ref> On 22 April, he suffered a torn hamstring while taking a penalty in a 1–0 win against [[Celta Vigo]], which ruled him out for the rest of the 2025–26 season.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Marsden |first=Sam |date=23 April 2026 |title=Barcelona's Lamine Yamal out for season, expected to make World Cup |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/story/_/id/48569662/barcelona-lamine-yamal-season-expected-fit-world-cup |work=ESPN}}</ref>

== International career ==

=== Catalonia ===
Yamal represented the youth sections of the [[Catalonia national football team]] from a young age, and became captain when he was 11 years old. He was captain throughout his time playing for the under-12, under-14 and under-16 teams.<ref>{{Cite web |date=12 September 2023 |title=Lamine Yamal, de les Seleccions Catalanes base a trencar rècords amb La Roja |url=https://www.fcf.cat/noticia/lamine-yamal-de-les-seleccions-catalanes-base-a-trencar-records-amb-la-roja/12/09/2023 |website=FCF |language=ca |access-date=16 July 2024 |archive-date=25 July 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240725002155/https://www.fcf.cat/noticia/lamine-yamal-de-les-seleccions-catalanes-base-a-trencar-records-amb-la-roja/12/09/2023 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name=":0">{{Cite web |date=20 November 2022 |title=Empat suficient per a la Selecció Catalana sub 16 |url=https://www.fcf.cat/noticia/empat-suficient-per-a-la-seleccio-catalana-sub-16/20/11/2022 |website=FCF |language=ca |access-date=16 July 2024 |archive-date=25 July 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240725002109/https://www.fcf.cat/noticia/empat-suficient-per-a-la-seleccio-catalana-sub-16/20/11/2022 |url-status=live }}</ref>

In November 2022, Yamal scored an impressive solo goal in a match against [[Castile and León autonomous football team|Castile and León]],<ref>{{Cite web |last=Ruano |first=Raúl |date=2024-07-10 |title=El golazo de Lamine Yamal en los anexos del Zorrilla con 15 años |url=https://www.diariodevalladolid.es/deportes/240710/230620/golazo-lamine-yamal-anexos-zorrilla-15-anos.html |access-date=2024-07-16 |website=Diario de Valladolid |language=es |archive-date=25 July 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240725002132/https://www.diariodevalladolid.es/deportes/240710/230620/golazo-lamine-yamal-anexos-zorrilla-15-anos.html |url-status=live }}</ref> and later that month he converted a penalty, provided the assist for Catalonia's second goal, and received a red card in a 2–2 draw with [[Aragon official football team|Aragon]] that sent Catalonia through to the "Fase d'Or" of the 2022–23 Spanish regional team championship.<ref name=":0" /> Yamal was not called up to the squad for the Fase d'Or in 2023.<ref>{{Cite web |date=4 January 2023 |title=Convocatòria d'entrenament sub 16 masculina: 10.01.23 |url=https://www.fcf.cat/noticia/convocatoria-d-entrenament-sub-16-masculina-10-01-23/04/01/2023 |website=FCF |language=ca |access-date=16 July 2024 |archive-date=25 July 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240725002204/https://www.fcf.cat/noticia/convocatoria-d-entrenament-sub-16-masculina-10-01-23/04/01/2023 |url-status=live }}</ref>

=== Spain ===
[[File:Lamine Yamal, Sánchez se reunió con los futbolistas de la selección española tras ganar la Eurocopa 2024 (3) (cropped).jpg|thumb|upright|Yamal celebrating the [[UEFA Euro 2024]] title with [[Spain national football team|Spain]]]]

Yamal was a youth international for Spain,<ref name=":5">{{Cite web |last=Peyret |first=Didac|title=¿Quién es Lamine Yamal? La perla de 15 años que ya entrena con Xavi |url=https://www.sport.es/es/noticias/barca/lamine-yamal-cadete-barcelona-xavi-13636159|date=4 September 2022|access-date=6 September 2022|website=[[Sport (Spanish newspaper)|Sport]] |language=es |archive-date=5 September 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220905220937/https://www.sport.es/es/noticias/barca/lamine-yamal-cadete-barcelona-xavi-13636159 |url-status=live }}</ref> having played for the [[Spain national under-15 football team|Spanish U15]] and [[Spain national under-16 football team|U16]] squads.<ref name=":2" /><ref>{{Cite web|title=Rojita U15 : Lamine Yamal s'éclate face à la Suisse (vidéo) |url=https://lionsdelatlas.ma/rojita-u15-lamine-yamal-seclate-face-a-la-suisse-video/|website=Lions de l'Atlas|date=7 May 2022|access-date=6 September 2022|language=fr |archive-date=9 September 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220909141432/https://lionsdelatlas.ma/rojita-u15-lamine-yamal-seclate-face-a-la-suisse-video/ |url-status=live }}</ref> In 2023, he represented [[Spain national under-17 football team|Spain's U17]] side in the [[2023 UEFA European Under-17 Championship|2023 European U17 Championship]] with Yamal scoring four goals during the tournament.<ref>{{cite web|first=Ángel|last=Álvarez|title=Lamine Yamal se despide del Europeo sub-17 con otro golazo antológico: es un elegido |url=https://cronicaglobal.elespanol.com/culemania/culemaniacos/20230530/lamine-yamal-despide-europeo-sub-17-antologico-elegido/767673315_0.html |website=Crónica Global |language=es |date=30 May 2023 |access-date=24 August 2023 |archive-date=24 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230824222830/https://cronicaglobal.elespanol.com/culemania/culemaniacos/20230530/lamine-yamal-despide-europeo-sub-17-antologico-elegido/767673315_0.html |url-status=live }}</ref> Spain went all the way to the semi-finals where they were knocked out by [[France national under-17 football team|France]] following a 3–1 defeat.<ref>{{cite web |title=España cae con honores (1–3) ante Francia en las semifinales del Europeo |url=https://rfef.es/es/noticias/cronica-espana-francia-semifinales-euro |website=Royal Spanish Football Federation|language=es |date=30 May 2023 |access-date=24 August 2023 |archive-date=24 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230824222829/https://rfef.es/es/noticias/cronica-espana-francia-semifinales-euro |url-status=live }}</ref>

At the age of 16 years and 50 days, Yamal received his first [[Spain national football team|senior international]] call-up on 1 September 2023 by coach [[Luis de la Fuente (footballer, born 1961)|Luis de la Fuente]] for the [[UEFA Euro 2024 qualifying|UEFA Euro 2024 qualifiers]] against [[Georgia national football team|Georgia]] and [[Cyprus national football team|Cyprus]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://rfef.es/es/noticias/oficial-lista-de-convocados-para-los-partidos-contra-georgia-y-chipre|title=Oficial {{!}} Lista de convocados para los partidos contra Georgia y Chipre|publisher=Royal Spanish Football Federation|date=1 September 2023|language=es|access-date=1 September 2023|archive-date=1 September 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230901155535/https://rfef.es/es/noticias/oficial-lista-de-convocados-para-los-partidos-contra-georgia-y-chipre|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=16-year-old Barcelona talent subject to "suffocating pressure" during international selection decision|url=https://www.football-espana.net/2023/09/01/16-year-old-barcelona-talent-subject-to-suffocating-pressure-during-international-selection-decision|website=Football España |date=1 September 2023 |access-date=1 September 2023 |archive-date=6 September 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230906104949/https://www.football-espana.net/2023/09/01/16-year-old-barcelona-talent-subject-to-suffocating-pressure-during-international-selection-decision |url-status=live }}</ref> and made his senior debut against the former opponent on 8 September 2023, scoring in the 74th minute of a 7–1 victory.<ref name="ESPN 2023">{{Cite news|first=Sam|last=Marsden|title=Spain teen Yamal scores, breaks record on debut|url=https://www.espn.com.au/football/story/_/id/38353315/barcelonas-lamine-yamal-becomes-youngest-player-spain|website=ESPN|date=8 September 2023|access-date=9 September 2023|archive-date=9 September 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230909003219/https://www.espn.com.au/football/story/_/id/38353315/barcelonas-lamine-yamal-becomes-youngest-player-spain|url-status=live}}</ref> At the age of 16 years and 57 days old, he became the youngest player and goalscorer for Spain, breaking records held by [[Gavi (footballer)|Gavi]] who debuted aged 17 years, 62 days and scored aged 17 years, 304 days.<ref>{{Cite news|title=Yamal becomes Spain's youngest player and scorer|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/66679258#:~:text=Barcelona%20teenager%20Lamine%20Yamal%20became,2024%20qualifying%20win%20against%20Georgia.|website=BBC Sport|publisher=BBC|date=9 September 2023}}</ref> Apart from this, Yamal became the youngest goalscorer in a Euro qualifying match, overtaking Welsh footballer [[Gareth Bale]] who scored at the age of 17 years, 83 days old.<ref name="ESPN 2023"/><ref>{{cite web |title=Lamine Yamal becomes youngest Spain player and scorer in rout of Georgia |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/sep/08/lamine-yamal-becomes-spains-youngest-ever-player-and-scorer |website=The Guardian |publisher=P. A. Media |date=8 September 2023 |access-date=9 September 2023 |archive-date=22 November 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231122032629/https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/sep/08/lamine-yamal-becomes-spains-youngest-ever-player-and-scorer |url-status=live }}</ref> Yamal was recalled to the Spanish squad in October 2023 for the remaining Euro qualifying matches against [[Scotland national football team|Scotland]] and [[Norway national football team|Norway]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Lamine Yamal: Iliopsoas muscle injury in left leg |url=https://www.fcbarcelona.com/en/football/first-team/news/3731723/lamine-yamal-iliopsoas-muscle-injury-in-left-leg |publisher=FC Barcelona |access-date=16 October 2023 |date=9 October 2023 |archive-date=17 October 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231017095117/https://www.fcbarcelona.com/en/football/first-team/news/3731723/lamine-yamal-iliopsoas-muscle-injury-in-left-leg |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Marsden |first1=Sam |last2=Llorens |first2=Moises |title=Barça injuries mount as Yamal out of Spain team |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/story/_/id/38621372/barcelona-injury-crisis-worsens-yamal-spain-squad |website=ESPN |date=10 October 2023 |access-date=16 October 2023 |archive-date=25 July 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240725002213/https://platform.twitter.com/widgets/widget_iframe.2f70fb173b9000da126c79afe2098f02.html?origin=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.espn.com |url-status=live }}</ref> Spain won both matches to qualify for [[UEFA Euro 2024|Euro 2024]].<ref>{{cite magazine|first=Robert|last=Summerscales|title=Scotland And Spain Qualify For Euro 2024 |url=https://www.si.com/fannation/soccer/futbol/news/scotland-and-spain-qualify-for-euro-2024-as-norway-miss-out |magazine=Sports Illustrated |date=15 October 2023|access-date=16 October 2023|archive-date=22 October 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231022014010/https://www.si.com/fannation/soccer/futbol/news/scotland-and-spain-qualify-for-euro-2024-as-norway-miss-out |url-status=live }}</ref>

On 7 June 2024, Yamal was selected in the 26-man squad for the tournament.<ref>{{cite news |date=7 June 2024 |title=Official {{!}} Final Spain squad for the Euro 2024 finals |url=https://rfef.es/en/noticias/final-spain-squad-for-the-euro-2024-finals |publisher=[[Royal Spanish Football Federation]] |access-date=7 June 2024 |archive-date=21 June 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240621100501/https://rfef.es/en/noticias/final-spain-squad-for-the-euro-2024-finals |url-status=live }}</ref> On 15 June, he made his debut in the European Championship against [[Croatia national football team|Croatia]], becoming the youngest player to feature in the tournament, aged 16 years and 338 days, breaking the previous record of Poland's [[Kacper Kozłowski (footballer)|Kacper Kozłowski]].<ref>{{cite news |last=Pellizzeri |first=Teo |url=https://sport.optus.com.au/news/uefa-euro-2024/os75853/lamine-yamal-breaks-record-youngest-euro-player |title=Prodigy Lamine Yamal breaks record as youngest ever UEFA Euro player |work=Optus Sport |date=15 June 2024 |archive-date=8 July 2024 |access-date=15 June 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240708171327/https://sport.optus.com.au/news/uefa-euro-2024/os75853/lamine-yamal-breaks-record-youngest-euro-player |url-status=live }}</ref> During the match against Croatia he also became the youngest player to provide an assist, setting up [[Dani Carvajal]]'s goal in a 3–0 victory.<ref>{{cite web |last=Mills |first=Richard |url=https://www.goal.com/en/lists/spain-player-ratings-croatia-lamine-yamal-alvaro-morata/blt4cadab491a033fd2#cs283e6bb2a786e738 |title=Spain player ratings vs Croatia: Lamine Yamal is unbelievable! Record-breaking teenager stars as La Roja make easy work of Luka Modric & Co in strong start to Euro 2024 |website=Goal |date=15 June 2024 |access-date=15 June 2024 |archive-date=25 July 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240725002136/https://www.goal.com/en/lists/spain-player-ratings-croatia-lamine-yamal-alvaro-morata/blt4cadab491a033fd2#cs283e6bb2a786e738 |url-status=live }}</ref> In the round of 16 match against Georgia, he became the youngest player to feature in the knockout phase, breaking [[Jude Bellingham]]'s record, in addition to providing another assist in a 4–1 victory.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/euro2024/news/028e-1b422f0a13e9-95e80bebdabb-1000--spain-4-1-georgia-resilient-la-roja-fight-back-to-reach-la/ |title=Spain 4-1 Georgia: Resilient La Roja fight back to reach quarter-finals |publisher=UEFA |date=30 June 2024 |access-date=30 June 2024 |archive-date=30 June 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240630212420/https://www.uefa.com/euro2024/news/028e-1b422f0a13e9-95e80bebdabb-1000--spain-4-1-georgia-resilient-la-roja-fight-back-to-reach-la/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

Yamal again provided a vital assist against [[Germany national football team|Germany]] in a 2–1 quarter-final win, and tied a Spanish record for having three assists in the same edition of the European Championship (after [[Cesc Fàbregas]] in [[UEFA Euro 2008|2008]], [[David Silva]] in [[UEFA Euro 2012|2012]] and [[Dani Olmo]] in [[UEFA Euro 2020|2020]]).<ref>{{Cite news|first=Aditya|last=Gokhale|title=Starboy! Lamine Yamal matches incredible Spain record at 16 after providing brilliant assist in Euro 2024 quarter-final clash with Germany|url=https://www.msn.com/en-us/sports/soccer/starboy-lamine-yamal-matches-incredible-spain-record-at-16-after-providing-brilliant-assist-in-euro-2024-quarter-final-clash-with-germany/ar-BB1pu9W6|website=[[MSNBC]]|date=5 July 2024}}</ref> He scored Spain's first goal in the 2–1 semi-final victory against [[France national football team|France]] on 9 July, with a curling strike from outside the penalty area, which won goal of the tournament.<ref name="BBCborn24">{{Cite news|first=Gary|last=Rose|title="A superstar is born" {{!}} Yamal's history making moment of "genius"|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/articles/cx82xyynw17o|website=[[BBC Sport]]|publisher=[[BBC]]|date=10 July 2024|archive-date=10 July 2024|access-date=24 July 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240710154821/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/articles/cx82xyynw17o|url-status=live}}</ref> He became the [[UEFA European Championship records and statistics|youngest goalscorer]] in the history of the Euros four days before his 17th birthday,<ref>{{Cite web|first=Jesse|last=Yomtov|title=Spain's Lamine Yamal nets sizzling goal, becomes youngest goal scorer in UEFA Euro history|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/sports/soccer/2024/07/09/lamine-yamal-goal-spain-euro-2024/74342111007/|website=USA Today|date=9 July 2024|access-date=9 July 2024|archive-date=15 July 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240715071348/https://www.usatoday.com/story/sports/soccer/2024/07/09/lamine-yamal-goal-spain-euro-2024/74342111007/|url-status=live}}</ref> and more than a year younger than the previous record holder [[Johan Vonlanthen]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Spain's Lamine Yamal, 16, 'genius' in Euro record evening|url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/story/_/id/40527430/spain-lamine-yamal-16-youngest-euro-scorer|website=[[ESPN]]|date=9 July 2024|access-date=10 July 2024|archive-date=15 July 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240715181647/https://www.espn.com/soccer/story/_/id/40527430/spain-lamine-yamal-16-youngest-euro-scorer|url-status=live}}</ref> At the end of Euro 2024, Yamal was named [[UEFA European Championship awards|Young Player of the Tournament]].<ref name="Euro24 YoungPlayer">{{Cite web|title=Lamine Yamal named Euro 2024 Young Player of the Tournament|url=https://www.uefa.com/euro2024/news/028f-1b5e5e91b6e6-b9784b9e13fb-1000--lamine-yamal-named-euro-2024-young-player-of-the-tournament/|website=UEFA|date=14 July 2024|access-date=14 July 2024|archive-date=15 July 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240715145905/https://www.uefa.com/euro2024/news/028f-1b5e5e91b6e6-b9784b9e13fb-1000--lamine-yamal-named-euro-2024-young-player-of-the-tournament/|url-status=live}}</ref> Spain's 2–1 victory against [[England national football team|England]] in the [[UEFA Euro 2024 final|Euro 2024 final]] made him the youngest player to win the Euros.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Lamine Yamal sets new record as youngest player to feature at a UEFA European Championship|url=https://www.uefa.com/euro2024/news/0255-0d9f33ac425a-2e8c3765087b-1000--lamine-yamal-sets-new-record-as-youngest-player-to-feature-a/|website=UEFA|date=14 July 2024|access-date=14 July 2024|archive-date=16 June 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240616091736/https://www.uefa.com/euro2024/news/0255-0d9f33ac425a-2e8c3765087b-1000--lamine-yamal-sets-new-record-as-youngest-player-to-feature-a/|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/euro2024/match/2036211--spain-vs-england/ |title=Spain vs England UEFA Euro 2024 Final |publisher=[[UEFA]] |date=14 July 2024 |access-date=16 July 2024 |archive-date=25 July 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240725002752/https://www.uefa.com/euro2024/match/2036211--spain-vs-england/ |url-status=live }}</ref> He assisted fellow winger [[Nico Williams]] for Spain's first goal in the final, subsequently becoming the youngest player to register a goal involvement in a major tournament final and becoming joint holder for the most assists in a single euro tournament with four assists.<ref name="Euro24 stats">{{cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/euro2024/news/028f-1b5e5c2b7b67-d5faab9be20b-1000--spain-2-1-england-late-oyarzabal-winner-earns-la-roja-reco/ |title=Spain 2-1 England: Late Oyarzabal winner earns La Roja record fourth Euro crown |website=UEFA |date=14 July 2024 |access-date=16 July 2024 |archive-date=15 July 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240715014101/https://www.uefa.com/euro2024/news/028f-1b5e5c2b7b67-d5faab9be20b-1000--spain-2-1-england-late-oyarzabal-winner-earns-la-roja-reco/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

In the [[2024–25 UEFA Nations League]], Yamal scored two goals – including his first professional career penalty – in a 5–4 semi-final victory against France.<ref>{{Cite web |last=read |first=The Canadian Press·2 min |date=2025-06-05 |title=Yamal outshines Ballon d'Or contenders as Spain beats France 5-4 in Nations League semifinal |url=https://ca.sports.yahoo.com/news/yamal-outshines-ballon-d-contenders-211000553.html |access-date=2025-06-05 |website=Yahoo Sports |language=en-US}}</ref>

==Player profile==
A left-footed forward with elite dribbling, excellent passing and chance-creating abilities, Yamal is able to play either as a [[centre-forward]], an [[attacking midfielder]] or a [[Winger (association football)|winger]], notably on the right flank.<ref name=Corbella /> As a [[Winger (football)|right-winger]], the majority of the time he likes to play with his left foot; he also has the ability to play outswinging [[Cross (association football)|crosses]] to the far post.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Lamine Yamal position and style of play|url=https://www.coachesvoice.com/cv/barcelona-extraordinary-talent-lamine-yamal-style-of-play/|website=The Coaches' Voice|access-date=9 May 2024|archive-date=25 July 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240725002747/https://www.coachesvoice.com/cv/barcelona-extraordinary-talent-lamine-yamal-style-of-play/|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.dw.com/en/spains-lamine-yamal-becomes-youngest-euros-player/a-69374470 |title=Spain's Lamine Yamal becomes youngest ever Euros player – DW – 06/15/2024 |website=dw.com |last1=Pearson |first1=Matt |date=15 June 2024 |access-date=22 June 2024 |archive-date=24 July 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240724080633/https://www.dw.com/en/spains-lamine-yamal-becomes-youngest-euros-player/a-69374470 |url-status=live }}</ref> His ability to produce accurate crosses with the outside of his foot (known as a ''[[trivela]]'') has become one of the trademarks of his game.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.sport.es/es/noticias/barca/trivela-lamine-asombra-mundo-marca-112311163 |title=La 'trivela' de Lamine asombra al mundo y ya es marca registrada |website=sport.es |last1=Peyret |first1=Dídac |date=4 December 2024 |access-date=6 April 2025 |language=es |archive-date=7 December 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241207091451/https://www.sport.es/es/noticias/barca/trivela-lamine-asombra-mundo-marca-112311163 |url-status=live }}</ref>

Yamal had a notable performance in the [[UEFA Euro 2024]], scoring a goal against [[France national football team|France]] in the semi-finals and providing a total of four assists against [[Croatia national football team|Croatia]], [[Georgia national football team|Georgia]], [[Germany national football team|Germany]], and [[England national football team|England]].<ref name="Euro24 stats"/> In this tournament, Yamal showcased his proficiency in creating chances by putting crosses towards the far-post, as well as his shot-taking and curling ability from distance.<ref name="Euro24 YoungPlayer"/>

With his technical profile, Yamal was compared to former Barcelona footballer [[Lionel Messi]], like many [[La Masia]] products before him.<ref name=Corbella /> Yamal has also drawn comparisons with former Barcelona player [[Neymar]] due to their similar playing style that involve a lot of dribbling, flair and chance creations.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.si.com/soccer/how-lamine-yamal-compares-to-lionel-messi-neymar-100-barcelona-games |title=How Lamine Yamal Compares to Lionel Messi, Neymar After 100 Barcelona Games?}}</ref> Yamal has also stated Neymar to be a major influence to the way he plays.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.fourfourtwo.com/features/who-is-lamine-yamal-everything-you-need-to-know-about-the-barcelona-wonderkid-barca-uncover-the-next-lionel-messi |title=Who is Lamine Yamal? Everything you need to know about the Barcelona wonderkid |publisher=fourfourtwo.com |last1=Dabbs |first1=Ryan |date=21 September 2023 |access-date=21 June 2024 |archive-date=15 July 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240715162632/https://www.fourfourtwo.com/features/who-is-lamine-yamal-everything-you-need-to-know-about-the-barcelona-wonderkid-barca-uncover-the-next-lionel-messi |url-status=live }}</ref> He has been described by media sources as being the best young footballer in the world;<ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-03-19 |title=Lamine Yamal: The greatest teenage footballer the world has ever seen {{!}} Goal.com |url=https://www.goal.com/en/lists/lamine-yamal-greatest-teenage-footballer-world-ever-seen/bltd659e03a46dcf8ed |access-date=2025-05-03 |website=www.goal.com |language=en |archive-date=30 March 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250330200315/https://www.goal.com/en/lists/lamine-yamal-greatest-teenage-footballer-world-ever-seen/bltd659e03a46dcf8ed |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-04-03 |title=Who are the 39 best men's U21 players in the world? |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/insider/story/_/id/44135155/yamal-wirtz-bellingham-lead-espn-39-best-male-players-age-21-under |access-date=2025-05-03 |website=ESPN.com |language=en |archive-date=6 April 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250406195929/https://www.espn.com/soccer/insider/story/_/id/44135155/yamal-wirtz-bellingham-lead-espn-39-best-male-players-age-21-under |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-10-29 |title=Lamine Yamal, the best young player in the world |url=https://www.lavanguardia.com/mediterranean/20241029/10060829/lamine-yamal-best-young-player-world-kopa-ballon-or-chatelet-paris-barcelona-spain-soccer-player.html |access-date=2025-05-03 |website=La Vanguardia |language=en |archive-date=6 November 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241106123533/https://www.lavanguardia.com/mediterranean/20241029/10060829/lamine-yamal-best-young-player-world-kopa-ballon-or-chatelet-paris-barcelona-spain-soccer-player.html |url-status=live }}</ref> many media outlets have praised him as the best teenage footballer ever,<ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-05-09 |title=Why Lamine Yamal is already better than Messi in some ways, but still has room to improve |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/story/_/id/45057444/why-lamine-yamal-already-better-messi-some-ways |access-date=2025-05-18 |website=ESPN.com |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-03-19 |title=Lamine Yamal: The greatest teenage footballer the world has ever seen {{!}} Goal.com UK |url=https://www.goal.com/en-gb/lists/lamine-yamal-greatest-teenage-footballer-world-ever-seen/bltd659e03a46dcf8ed |access-date=2025-05-18 |website=www.goal.com |language=en-GB}}</ref> though many, including [[Steven Gerrard]], state that [[Michael Owen]] remains the best.<ref>{{Cite web |title= Gerrard: Owen better as teenager than 'incredible' Yamal, Mbappé |url= https://www.espn.co.uk/football/story/_/id/45924367/steven-gerrard-michael-owen-better-player-teenager-lamine-yamal-kylian-mbappe |access-date=2025-09-22 |website=ESPN UK |language=en-GB}}</ref>

==Personal life==
In July 2025, Spain's Ministry of Social Rights asked the country's prosecutor's office to investigate Yamal, after it was alleged that he had hired several people with [[dwarfism]] to perform at his 18th birthday party.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-07-15 |title=Lamine Yamal: Barcelona winger set to be investigated over dwarfism row |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/articles/cn5kpd4y2yvo |access-date=2025-07-15 |website=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref>

Yamal was briefly in a relationship with [[Nicki Nicole]], an Argentinian singer, though the two separated in October 2025.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://people.com/who-is-nicki-nicole-lamine-yamal-11797013 |title=Who Is Lamine Yamal's Girlfriend? All About Grammy-Nominated Singer Nicki Nicole |website=People |date=2025 |access-date=20 September 2025}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=1 November 2025 |title=Barcelona's Lamine Yamal announces Nicki Nicole breakup – Get Spanish Football News |url=https://getfootballnewsspain.com/barcelonas-lamine-yamal-announces-nicki-nicole-breakup/ |access-date=1 November 2025 |website=getfootballnewsspain.com |language=en-US}}</ref>

===Family===
Yamal was born to Sheila Ebana, a waitress from [[Bata, Equatorial Guinea]], and Mounir Nasraoui, a building painter from [[Larache]], Morocco.<ref name="espn">{{cite web |last1=Marsden |first1=Sam |last2=Llorens |first2=Moises |title=The story of 16-year-old Lamine Yamal, destined to be Barcelona's next superstar |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/story/_/id/38354902/the-story-16-year-old-lamine-yamal-barca-next-superstar |website=ESPN |access-date=10 July 2024 |date=10 September 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240615143216/https://www.espn.com/soccer/story/_/id/38354902/the-story-16-year-old-lamine-yamal-barca-next-superstar |archive-date=15 June 2024}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Billebault |first1=Alexis |title=Lamine Yamal, le surdoué du foot que tout le Maroc attend - Jeune Afrique.com |url=https://www.jeuneafrique.com/1555586/societe/lamine-yamal-le-surdoue-du-foot-que-tout-le-maroc-attend/ |website=JeuneAfrique |access-date=10 July 2024 |language=fr|date=10 April 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240604110717/https://www.jeuneafrique.com/1555586/societe/lamine-yamal-le-surdoue-du-foot-que-tout-le-maroc-attend/ |archive-date=4 June 2024}}</ref> His parents separated when he was three, although both remained present through his childhood.<ref name="ausarticle" /> The family had lived in [[Mataró]], but around the time of his parents' separation, Yamal's mother moved to Granollers.<ref name=Herrero/> He would alternate between both cities to spend time with his parents.<ref name="ausarticle">{{cite web |last1=Ducker |first1=James |title=Meeting Messi as a baby, stunners for his country at 16. Welcome to the world of Lamine Yamal |url=https://www.smh.com.au/sport/soccer/euro-2024-semi-finals-spain-france-england-netherlands-20240710-p5jsdy.html |website=The Sydney Morning Herald |access-date=10 July 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240709213633/https://www.smh.com.au/sport/soccer/euro-2024-semi-finals-spain-france-england-netherlands-20240710-p5jsdy.html |archive-date=9 July 2024 |date=10 July 2024}}</ref> He has a younger half-brother named Keyne (born 2022) and a younger half-sister named Baraa.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Mishra |first=Abhishek |date=2024-07-14 |title=Who Is Lamine Yamal's Mother? Meet Sheila Ebana, the Woman Behind the Spain Star's Viral Pic With Lionel Messi |url=https://www.essentiallysports.com/soccer-football-news-who-is-lamine-yamal-mother-meet-sheila-ebana-the-woman-behind-the-spain-star-viral-pic-with-lionel-messi/ |access-date=2025-05-06 |website=EssentiallySports |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Shigjeqi |first=Egzona |date=2024-10-29 |title=Lamine Yamal's younger brother stole all the attention at the Ballon d'Or ceremony - Telegraph |url=https://telegrafi.com/en/Lamine-Yamal%27s-younger-brother-stole-all-the-attention-at-the-Ballon-d%27Or-ceremony/ |access-date=2025-05-06 |language=en |archive-date=12 May 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250512010831/https://telegrafi.com/en/Lamine-Yamal%27s-younger-brother-stole-all-the-attention-at-the-Ballon-d%27Or-ceremony/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

On 14 August 2024, Yamal's father was stabbed in a car park in Mataró;<ref>{{cite web |date=14 August 2024 |title=El padre de Lamine Yamal apuñalado en un parking de Mataró |url=https://www.lavanguardia.com/sucesos/20240814/9871540/padre-lamine-yamal-apunalado-parking-mataro.html |access-date=14 August 2024 |publisher=La Vanguardia |archive-date=17 August 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240817050950/https://www.lavanguardia.com/sucesos/20240814/9871540/padre-lamine-yamal-apunalado-parking-mataro.html |url-status=live }}</ref> his injuries were minor, and he was discharged from hospital three days later. Police arrested four people involved in the attack.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-08-15 |title=Lamine Yamal's father stabbed, four people arrested for alleged attempted murder |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/5701622/2024/08/15/lamine-yamal-father-attack/ |website=The Athletic |access-date=15 August 2024 |archive-date=24 August 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240824091015/https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/5701622/2024/08/15/lamine-yamal-father-attack/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-08-16 |title=Barcelona star Lamine Yamal's father discharged from hospital after brutal stabbing attack {{!}} Goal.com US |url=https://www.goal.com/en-us/lists/barcelona-star-lamine-yamal-s-father-discharged-from-hospital-after-brutal-stabbing-attack/blt1b65e541a13bda15 |access-date=2024-10-29 |website=www.goal.com |language=en-US |archive-date=16 August 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240816183951/https://www.goal.com/en-us/lists/barcelona-star-lamine-yamal-s-father-discharged-from-hospital-after-brutal-stabbing-attack/blt1b65e541a13bda15 |url-status=live }}</ref>

===Activism===
Yamal, who is a practising Muslim,<ref>{{cite web |last1=Jackson |first1=Bobbie |title=Lamine Yamal condemns racist abuse heard during Spain v Egypt friendly |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/articles/cz6737pdnwpo |website=BBC Sport |access-date=12 May 2026 |date=1 April 2026}}</ref> condemned [[Islamophobic]] and [[xenophobic]] chants directed at Egyptian players by Spanish fans during Spain's friendly match against Egypt in Barcelona on 31 March 2026. In a statement, he said that the chants "were aimed at the opposing team and were not something personal against me, but as a Muslim, it is still a lack of respect and something intolerable."<ref>{{cite news |title=Lamine Yamal furious with Spain fans over anti-Muslim chants against Egypt |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2026/apr/01/spain-fans-islamophobic-and-xenophobic-chants-egypt-police-investigate⁠ |website=The Guardian |date=1 April 2026 |access-date=2 April 2026}}</ref>

During Barcelona's La Liga title-winning parade on 11 May 2026, Yamal showed solidarity with [[Palestinians]] by waving a [[Palestinian flag]]. His action was praised by fans, pro-Palestinian activists, and politicians such as the Prime Minister of Spain [[Pedro Sánchez]], while it also drew criticism from Israeli defense minister [[Israel Katz]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Lamine Yamal’s Palestine flag wave hailed by fans, activists and athletes |website=[[Al Jazeera]] |date=12 May 2026 |url=https://www.aljazeera.com/sports/2026/5/12/lamine-yamals-palestine-flag-wave-hailed-by-fans-activists-and-athletes |access-date=13 May 2026}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Israel Minister Criticises Lamine Yamal Over Palestinian Flag at Barcelona Title Parade |url=https://dailypioneer.com/news/slug-lite/israeli-minister-criticizes-yamal-for-waving-palestinian-flag?year=2026 |access-date=2026-05-17 |website=[[dailypioneer.com]] |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2026-05-15 |title=FC Barcelona says 'no comment' on Israel's accusation against Yamal |url=https://www.euronews.com/my-europe/2026/05/15/fc-barcelona-tells-euronews-no-comment-after-israel-accuses-yamal-of-fuelling-hatred |access-date=2026-05-17 |website=[[Euronews]] |language=en}}</ref> [[Misbar]], a [[fact-checking]] website, reported that Yamal was targeted in a social media campaign that sought to link the Palestinian flag to terrorism.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.misbar.com/en/editorial/2026/05/31/misbar-analyzes-digital-campaign-targeting-lamine-yamal-after-he-raised-palestinian-flag|title=MISBAR Analyzes Digital Campaign Targeting Lamine Yamal After He Raised the Palestinian Flag|date=June 1, 2026|website=[[Misbar]]}}</ref>

